courses.learning_outcomes:
1) Be able to arrive at clinical formulation by analyzing case-based clinical information from multiple biopsychosocial perspectives;
2) Be able to work out and prioritize the clinical management areas in a realistic time-frame and clinical setting;
3) Be able to work out clinical solutions specific to the clinical focus based on evidence-based practice and collaborative multidisciplinary approach;
4) Be able to link clinical presentations of the disease to the relevant basic neuroscience, psychopharmacology, psychology and social contexts;
5) Be able to formulate research question out of the clinical dilemma and rigorously search scientific evidence to arrive at evidence-based management approaches;
6) Be able to communicate effectively ideas on case formulation and management with a multidisciplinary peer professional
